Package: fitnmr
Version: 1.0
Title: Multidimensional NMR Spectrum Peak Fitting and Analysis
Authors@R: c(person("Colin", "Smith", role=c("aut", "cre"),
                    email = "colin.smith@wesleyan.edu"))
Author: Colin Smith [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Colin Smith <colin.smith@wesleyan.edu>
Description: Tools for fitting and analyzing 1D-4D NMR peaks with analytical
    lineshape models and multiplet parameterizations. The package reads
    NMRPipe format spectra, builds constrained parameter/group structures
    (chemical shifts, linewidths, amplitudes, phases, and scalar couplings),
    and performs nonlinear least-squares optimization for single fits or
    iterative peak discovery with F-test-based acceptance. It includes methods
    to visualize data, model fits, and sparse spectral regions. For 1D time
    series workflows, it also supports preprocessing and kinetic analysis,
    including automated phase optimization, solvent suppression, FID-based
    correction of frequency shifts/line broadening, and two-state plus
    exponential rate fitting. See references Dudley et al. (2020)
    <doi:10.1016/j.jmr.2020.106773>, Syed et al. (2024)
    <doi:10.5194/mr-5-103-2024>, and Blejec et al. (2026)
    <doi:10.1002/pro.70508>.
